frontmatter.title: Decompilation Analysis Report
frontmatter.subtitle: Examining Code Recovery Across Compiler Optimization Levels

children.value: This experiment analyzes how compiler optimizations affect the ability to recover source code through decompilation. A simple C program was compiled with three optimization levels (
to compare what information can and cannot be reconstructed.

: While control flow and logic are largely recoverable, semantic information like variable names, comments, and developer intent are permanently lost. Higher optimizations dramatically transform code structure.
